<item>
            <title>[PDFBOX-2371] Overlay page off by one when using -useAllPages</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2371</link>
                <project id="12310760" key="PDFBOX">PDFBox</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When using the new -useAllPages option added in 1.8.7, the usePageNum doesn&apos;t account for the fact that the specificOverlayPage is indexed by zero and the output ends up with overlay pages shifted&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;e.g. The output page 1 has page 2 from the overlay.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We need to subtract 1 from the pageNumber when getting the overlay page number.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;int usePageNum = (pageNumber - 1) % numberOfOverlayPages;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
